13:07.227 --> 13:09.564
Hey.
Are you awake?

13:11.198 --> 13:13.434
Yeah, baby.
What is it?

13:15.735 --> 13:18.171
You were having a bad dream.

13:19.473 --> 13:20.675
Uh-huh.

13:21.842 --> 13:23.444
What was it about?

13:29.315 --> 13:31.118
I can't remember.

13:36.556 --> 13:39.659
Sometimes I wonder if we should
move away from this place.

13:45.199 --> 13:46.832
Where?

13:46.834 --> 13:48.469
I don't know.

13:50.536 --> 13:52.139
No.

13:53.440 --> 13:55.142
I like it here.

13:57.210 --> 13:59.778
It's peaceful here, right?
This is, like, our little...

13:59.780 --> 14:01.749
This is our little home.

14:08.421 --> 14:09.888
Did I ever tell you
about the starlings

14:09.890 --> 14:11.626
when I was a little kid?

14:14.261 --> 14:16.227
No. I don't think so.

14:16.229 --> 14:17.862
In the neighborhood
where I grew up,

14:17.864 --> 14:21.533
there were all these starlings
flying around in the trees,

14:21.535 --> 14:24.137
playing and chirping,
and they were so cute.

14:26.607 --> 14:28.342
But my dad...

14:29.810 --> 14:32.577
...he just hated them

14:32.579 --> 14:36.084
'cause they were always eating
cherries from the cherry tree.

14:38.785 --> 14:40.555
Anyway, one day...

14:42.522 --> 14:44.823
One day, me and a bunch of the
other kids from the neighborhood

14:44.825 --> 14:47.094
were playing in this empty lot.

14:48.161 --> 14:53.533
And my dad came walking across
with a pillowcase...

14:54.501 --> 14:56.571
...and a crowbar.

14:57.771 --> 15:01.606
And there was something moving
around inside of the pillowcase,

15:01.608 --> 15:03.377
like, squirming around.

15:04.177 --> 15:08.646
And he said we should
gather 'round.

15:08.648 --> 15:12.516
He had something to show us,
and so we all gathered 'round,

15:12.518 --> 15:16.224
and he emptied what was in
the pillowcase on the ground.

15:18.691 --> 15:20.327
And it was a...

15:23.497 --> 15:26.901
It was a bunch
of baby starlings.

15:29.335 --> 15:32.572
And he told us that he was gonna
show us how to kill them.

15:37.810 --> 15:41.181
And he lifted
the crowbar up real high...

15:43.849 --> 15:45.353
...and then...

15:46.987 --> 15:50.925
...brought it down real hard
on the little baby bird.

15:57.397 --> 16:00.598
So hard that it pushed it
in the ground.

16:00.600 --> 16:03.537
It was so deep in there,
like a little grave, you know?

16:10.978 --> 16:16.247
And then he gave the crowbar
to one of the kids, and then...

16:16.249 --> 16:19.384
each kid took a turn in...

16:19.386 --> 16:21.355
killing a starling.

16:32.766 --> 16:34.267
What'd you do?

16:38.638 --> 16:40.273
I, um...

16:45.679 --> 16:49.617
...just watched, and then when
it was my turn, I just ran away.

16:56.823 --> 16:58.559
Oh, baby.

16:59.526 --> 17:01.262
Come here.

17:23.717 --> 17:27.688
MANDY: <i>"Under the crimson,
primordial sky...</i>

17:28.755 --> 17:31.389
<i>...surrounded by
the jagged rocks</i>

17:31.391 --> 17:34.592
<i>of the ancient
volcanic mountain,</i>

17:34.594 --> 17:36.428
<i>the wretched Warlock</i>

17:36.430 --> 17:40.465
<i>reached into the dark embrace
of the fissure</i>

17:40.467 --> 17:44.034
<i>until his hand touched
a smooth glassy surface.</i>

17:44.036 --> 17:45.736
<i>Cold as ice.</i>

17:45.738 --> 17:49.774
